      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY BETTOR HALF (9) has been freshened since she was a beaten favourite in a higher-graded race at Melton last start but was far from disgraced when beaten just 3 metres after racing parked. Broke her maiden in Adelaide prior. Hails from a leading yard and looks well placed in this line-up. IM WESLEY (1) has been competitive from wider barriers of late. Recoded back-to-back placings then kept the ball rolling last time when fifth after racing parked at this circuit and distance. Should enjoy a more economical run from this draw. CELESTIAL ZODIAC (12) may need luck from the back row but looks close to a win after two successive placings and he owns a good record at this distance. PISTOL PEARCE (6) is working up to a win having shown pleasing improvement last time out when runner-up at Cranbourne.",
